    "body": "@soltanmm The prefixes are used in the default install script (which points to some location owned by homebrew on both Linux and OS X):\n- [ruby](https://github.com/grpc/homebrew-grpc/blob/98889dade81d033ff2883d240264259f263054db/scripts/install#L93)\n- [node](https://github.com/grpc/homebrew-grpc/blob/98889dade81d033ff2883d240264259f263054db/scripts/install#L104)\n- [python](https://github.com/grpc/homebrew-grpc/blob/98889dade81d033ff2883d240264259f263054db/scripts/install#L115)\n\n---\n\nThe difference is the \"break apart\" I am mentioning. It really is the content of https://goo.gl/getgrpc that I am referring to, because installing from source already supports using any prefix you like.\n\nThe difference is that users won't want to / know how to install from source, so the recommended install should \"just work\" and the two scenarios above (local prefix vs. system `/usr`) reasonably cover this.\n"
  },
